# Always following for the following guidelines when writing/making/updating a help menu for a command-line program

- Always have a shortcut version and long form version args
- Always put the shortcut versions before the long form version
- Always put the required args in a group before the optional ones (if there are both kinds)
- Always 3 spaces to start the args line, then in next line 1 tab before writing the description
- Always leave 1 empty space before starting another arg

Example:
```
Required:
   -i INPUT, --input INPUT
	Input file or folder

   -d DATASET_NAME, --dataset-name DATASET_NAME
	Dataset name


Optionals:
   -t THREADS, --threads THREADS
	Number of threads to use
```